    "pathway": "Sentence Structure",
    "introduction": "Combine short sentences to make writing smoother and avoid repetition.",
    "stepByStep": "Combining short, choppy sentences helps your writing flow better. You can combine sentences using coordinating conjunctions (FANBOYS), subordinating conjunctions, or semicolons.<br><br>#### Coordinating Conjunctions<br>Join two related independent clauses using a comma and <em>for, and, nor, but, or, yet, so</em>.<br>- <strong>Example:</strong> I wanted to go to the park, <strong>but</strong> it started to rain.<br><br>#### Subordinating Conjunctions<br>Turn one sentence into a dependent clause to show the relationship between the two ideas.<br>- <strong>Example:</strong> <strong>Because</strong> it started to rain, I couldn't go to the park.<br><br>#### Semicolons<br>Use a semicolon to join two closely related independent clauses without a conjunction.<br>- <strong>Example:</strong> The sun is shining; the birds are singing."
