    "introduction": "<strong>What is a Sentence Fragment?</strong><br>A sentence fragment is an incomplete sentence. It is missing a subject, a verb, or it doesn't express a complete thought (like a dependent clause left by itself).<br><br>#### Examples of Fragments:<br>- <strong>Missing Subject:</strong> Went to the store. (Who went?)<br>- <strong>Missing Verb:</strong> The large, angry dog. (What did the dog do?)<br>- <strong>Incomplete Thought:</strong> Because I was tired. (What happened because you were tired?)<br><br>#### How to Fix Fragments:<br>1. Add the missing subject or verb.<br>2. Attach the dependent clause to an independent clause.<br><br><strong>Fragment:</strong> Because it was raining.<br><strong>Fixed:</strong> Because it was raining, we stayed indoors."
