    "introduction": "A practical repair guide and checklist to fix any broken sentence structure.",
    "stepByStep": "When editing your writing, follow this checklist to repair broken sentences:<br><br>1. <strong>Check for the core:</strong> Does the sentence have a clear subject and verb?<br>2. <strong>Check the boundaries:</strong> Does it start with a capital letter and end with proper punctuation? Are independent clauses separated correctly (no run-ons or comma splices)?<br>3. <strong>Check the logic:</strong> Do the parts of the sentence make sense together? Are modifiers in the right place? Are pronouns clear?<br>4. <strong>Check the length:</strong> Is it an overloaded sentence that needs to be broken up? Or is it too choppy and needs to be combined with another sentence?<br><br>By methodically checking these four areas, you can turn a confusing sentence into a clear and effective one."
