    "stepByStep": "<strong>The Rule:</strong> Indefinite pronouns that end in <em>-one, -body,</em> or <em>-thing</em> are ALWAYS SINGULAR. They take a singular verb (is, has, does, or Verb+s).<br><br><strong>The \"ONE\" Group:</strong><br>- Everyone, Someone, Anyone, No one<br>- <em>Everyone <strong>is</strong> here.</em><br><br><strong>The \"BODY\" Group:</strong><br>- Everybody, Somebody, Anybody, Nobody<br>- <em>Somebody <strong>has</strong> my keys.</em><br><br><strong>The \"THING\" Group:</strong><br>- Everything, Something, Anything, Nothing<br>- <em>Nothing <strong>matters</strong>.</em>",
