    "meaning": "The Subject and the Verb must agree, no matter how many words are between them. <br>Phrases that come between the subject and the verb are usually <strong>Prepositional Phrases</strong> or <strong>Relative Clauses</strong>. They add description, but they DO NOT change the number of the subject.",
